   "source": [
    "# Single sample intracellular signalling network inference\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook we showcase how to use the advanced CARNIVAL implementation available in CORNETO. This implementation extends the capabilities of the original CARNIVAL method by enabling advanced modelling and injection of knowledge for hypothesis generation. We will use a dataset consisting of 6 samples of hepatic stellate cells (HSC) where three of them were activated by the cytokine Transforming growth factor (TGF-β). \n",
    "\n",
    "In the first part, we will show how to estimate Transcription Factor activities from gene expression data, following the [Decoupler tutorial](https://decoupler-py.readthedocs.io/en/latest/notebooks/bulk.html) for functional analysis. Then, we will use the CARNIVAL method available in CORNETO to infer a network from TFs to receptors, assuming that we don't really know which treatment was used. We will see how to do some basic modeling and adding information from pathway enrichment using PROGENy to bias the inferred networks.\n",
    "\n",
    "> **NOTE:** This tutorial uses the new **Decoupler v2** version. We also use the **highs** solver, which has to be installed with `pip install highspy`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "95502198-c8a0-4d71-a5e9-709bad72ec00",

    "import omnipath as op\n",

    "# https://corneto.org\n",

   "source": [
    "# Build DESeq2 object\n",
    "inference = DefaultInference(n_cpus=8)\n",
    "dds = DeseqDataSet(\n",
    "    adata=adata,\n",
    "    design_factors=\"condition\",\n",
    "    refit_cooks=True,\n",
    "    inference=inference,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute LFCs\n",
    "dds.deseq2()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extract contrast between conditions\n",
    "stat_res = DeseqStats(dds, contrast=[\"condition\", \"treatment\", \"control\"], inference=inference)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute Wald test\n",
    "stat_res.summary()"
   ]

    "# Run\n",

    "tf_acts = tf_acts.loc[:, msk]\n",
    "\n",
    "tf_acts"
   ]

    "\n",
    "CORNETO is a unified framework for knowledge-driven network inference. It includes a very flexible implementation of CARNIVAL that expands its original capabilities.     ")"

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1a182f07-2ca6-4d4e-9e78-f9d655444750",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Changing modelling assumptions\n",
    "\n",
    "Thanks to CORNETO's modeling capabilities, we can manipulate the problems to add more knowledge, new objectives or different constraints. As an example, we are going to penalize the use of inhibitory interactions from the PKN to simplify the reconstructed networks in CARNIVAL"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "id": "be2f089d-7850-42d5-b295-29d17ae3e168",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(3279,)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 32,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "edge_interactions = np.array(carnival.processed_graph.get_attr_from_edges(\"interaction\"))\n",
    "penalties = np.zeros_like(edge_interactions)\n",
    "# We add a large penalty to each interaction which is inhibitory (-1)\n",
    "penalties[edge_interactions == -1] = 10\n",
    "penalties.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "id": "643fa0f2-a5a2-4fd2-a10c-9676c48d4432",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(1,)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 33,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# We use the edge_has_signal variable (1 if selected to propagate signal, 0 otherwise),\n",
    "# and we multiply with  the penalties\n",
    "(P.expr.edge_has_signal.T @ penalties).shape"
   ]
  },

    "# We extract the selected edges. Networks are simpler,\n",
    "# and they show again some activation of CDH2 and inhibition of IGF1\n",
    "sol_edges = np.flatnonzero(np.abs(P.expr.edge_value.value) > 0.5)\n",
    "carnival.processed_graph.plot_values(\n",
    "    vertex_values=P.expr.vertex_value.value,\n",
    "    edge_values=P.expr.edge_value.value,\n",
    "    edge_indexes=sol_edges,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "## Other options\n",
    "\n",
    "We included an option to simplify the networks inferred by CARNIVAL, by penalizing the selection of indirect rules. These rules are:\n",
    "- A -> B in the PKN, and we observe B is downregulated, we explain it with downregulation of its upstream gene A\n",
    "- A -| B in the PKN, and we observe B is upregulated, we explain it with downregulation of A\n",
    "\n",
    "> NOTE: This is an experimental feature and was not benchmarked in the original CARNIVAL paper. "
   ]
  },

   "id": "abb5b887-97bf-4261-9741-fd65e286728b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Using information from PROGENy\n",
    "\n",
    "In the previous examples, we used only information from TF activities and de-regulated receptors, and we tested different options. However, results can be highly variable, due to uncertainty in the intermediate signalling proteins (downstream receptors and upstream TFs), and due to the existence of multiple paths in the PKN.\n",
    "\n",
    "Additional information can be used to bias the reconstruction towards more plausible signalling pathways. Here, we will use information from PROGENy, which infers pathway activities from gene expression data."
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "df_progeny_with_de = progeny[(progeny.source == \"TGFb\")].set_index(\"target\").join(results_df, rsuffix=\"_deseq\")\n",
    "df_progeny_with_de = df_progeny_with_de[(df_progeny_with_de.padj_deseq <= 1e-2) & (df_progeny_with_de.padj <= 1e-2)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# We remove the TFs, we keep only unscored nodes in the network\n",
    "df_progeny_with_de = df_progeny_with_de.loc[df_progeny_with_de.index.difference(tf_acts.columns)]\n",
    "# We will calculate an score of importance, based on the weight from progeny PKN (the coefficient of importance)\n",
    "# and the stat from DESeq2 for that gene in our dataset\n",
    "df_progeny_with_de[\"score\"] = df_progeny_with_de[\"weight\"].abs() * df_progeny_with_de[\"stat\"].abs()\n",
    "df_progeny_with_de"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# We will favor now the inclusion of these genes. We will\n",
    "# increase lambda to get smaller networks for interpretation, and\n",
    "# we will use a large penalty for indirect rules.\n",
    "carnival = CarnivalFlow(lambda_reg=1.5, indirect_rule_penalty=1)\n",
    "P = carnival.build(G, data)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# We need to select the subset of genes in the processed graph, since after building carnival using the\n",
    "# inputs (receptors) and TFs, the processed graph is pruned (unreachable genes removed) and thus many\n",
    "# of the genes we want to score are not anymore in the graph\n",
    "tgfb_genes = df_progeny_with_de.index.intersection(carnival.processed_graph.V).tolist()\n",
    "len(tgfb_genes)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# We can visualize only the genes in the pruned PKN that carnival will use\n",
    "# NOTE: The processed graph is the pruned PKN containing all interactions\n",
    "# connecting the selected receptors to TFs, before inferring the signalling\n",
    "# networks\n",
    "dc.pl.source_targets(\n",
    "    data=results_df.loc[tgfb_genes], x=\"weight\", y=\"stat\", net=progeny, name=\"TGFb\", top=15, figsize=(4, 4)\n",
    ")"
   ]

    "# Scale factor for influence in the overall CARNIVAL obj function\n",
    "influence_factor = 0.1\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create the custom obj function to include in CARNIVAL\n",
    "vertex_scores = np.zeros(len(carnival.processed_graph.V))\n",
    "vertex_selected_var = P.expr.vertex_activated + P.expr.vertex_inhibited\n",
    "for i, v in enumerate(carnival.processed_graph.V):\n",
    "    if v in tgfb_genes:\n",
    "        score = df_progeny_with_de.loc[v].score\n",
    "        vertex_scores[i] = score\n",
    "        print(i, v, score)\n",
    "\n",
    "# The objective is just c^T @ penalties\n",
    "obj = vertex_selected_var.T @ vertex_scores\n",
    "\n",
    "# We add a negative weight to maximize selection\n",
    "P.add_objective(obj, name=\"progeny_genes_score\", weight=-influence_factor)\n",
    "P.solve(solver=\"highs\", max_seconds=60, verbosity=1);"
   ]
  },

    "import cvxpy as cp\n",
    "\n",
    "carnival = CarnivalFlow(lambda_reg=0, indirect_rule_penalty=10)\n",
    "P = carnival.build(G, data)\n",
    "P.add_objective(obj, name=\"progeny_genes_score\", weight=-influence_factor)\n",
    "P.add_objective(P.expr.vertex_max_depth.apply(cp.max), weight=0.1)\n",
    "P.solve(solver=\"highs\", verbosity=1)"
   ]
